removed:
 - building readline.c and readline.o, obviously
 - $&readline et al in list of prims to init
 - @READLINE_LIBS@ (for -L and -l) and @READLINE_CFLAGS@ (for -I)

CURRENT build process:
 - .o files are built (incl. parser gen, mksignal, etc.)
 - esdump is linked - inputs: .o files
 - esdump runs initial.es
    - esdump produces initial.c
 - es is linked - inputs: initial.c, libs, cflag, ldflags

WANT build process:
 - core .o files are built (incl. parser gen, mksignal, etc.)
 - esdump is linked - inputs: .o files
 - esdump runs initial.es
    - initial.es calls library scripts
    - library scripts define .c/.o files, provide libs, cflags, ldflags
    - esdump produces initial.c
 - additional .o files are built with appropriate cflags
 - es is linked - inputs: initial.c, libs, cflags, ldflags

WANT more concretely:
 - core Makefile builds core .o files
 - core Makefile builds esdump
 - core Makefile runs esdump
    - esdump runs initial.es
       - initial.es sources library scripts
          - library scripts build .o files with their own CFLAGS
          - library scripts modify OFILES, LIBS, LDFLAGS, and normal es vars
    - esdump produces initial.c
    - esdump calls final Makefile with .o files, LIBS, LDFLAGS in env
       - final Makefile links es binary
